==Translingual==

===Cardinal number===
*[[w:Arabic numerals|Arabic numerals]]: 0
*[[w:Chinese numerals|Chinese numerals]]: [[零]], [[〇]]

===Pronunciation===
''See'' [[zero]]

====Pronunciation note====
The pronunciation of '''0''' (zero) as a [[digit]] is very often shortened to that of the letter '''[[o|O]]''' to save time or keep rhythm. This change is required for the [[tens place]] of [[minute]]s following the [[hour]] and in shortened pronunciation of numbers between 10 and 19 hundred, including [[year]]s, as well as their truncated two-digit forms, where the zero is a leading digit. It is also very common when saying [[telephone number]]s, [[decimals]] after the [[decimal point]], the [[leading zero]] in decimal fractions less than one, or many other words such as "[[007]]".

===Noun===
'''0''' (''plural:'' '''[[0s]]''')
# The [[cardinal number]] [[zero]] indicating absence of any quantity. 
#:''They scored '''0''' in their worst game yet.''
# [[numeral]] corresponding to the number zero.
#:''The flashing '''0''' indicates that time is up.''
# A [[digit]] in [[decimal]], [[binary]], and every other [[base]] numbering system.
<!--
#:''The Boolean domain contains only '''0''' and 1.'' not petinent to numbering
replace with:
