#:''Binary numbers ending in '''0''' are even.''
# The origin, starting point, or fixed reference point, especially for a measurement.
#:''The '''0''' for the Celcius scale is 273.15 Kelvin.''
# Nothing, nought.
#:''The shipment was lost, so they had '''0''' in stock.''
#{{mathematics}} The [[identity element]] with respect to [[addition]].
#: <math>\exists\,\mathbf{0}:\forall a\in A:\mathbf{0}+a=a+\mathbf{0}=a</math>
#(''computer science'' or ''electrical engineering'') [[bit]] state corresponding to binary digit 0 or [[FALSE]]; in a [[logic gate]] in the ''low'' state or [[off]].
#:''If the NOT gate input is 1, the output is '''0'''.''
#{{mathematics}} A [[Boolean]] or truth value corresponding to FALSE.
#:''If A&B&C='''0''' then  at least one of A, B, or C is '''0'''.''


